<div class="readingWelcome">
  <h2>J and P Metal Works specializes in metal wall art, metal signs, and metal fabrication services.<br><br>Based out of Spring Lake, North Carolina we provide local services to Fayetteville NC, Fort Bragg, Southern Pines, Hope Mills, and Sanford.<br><br>We provide shipping to all 50 states and offer international shipping as well!</h2>
</div>
<div class="moreReading">
  <div class="mrTitle"><h2 id="mrTitle">What can we make?</h2></div>
  <div class="mrBody"><h3>With high end machines and master craftsmanship, there is no project to big or small for us to make. Some of the most common requests are for business signs, Special Forces memorabilia for our Ft Bragg soldiers, metal cups and mugs, and various patriotic items such as artistic flags.<br><br>We work with our clients very closely to ensure that we supersede all expectations, as such, we can work with you on a custom design, paint scheme, and many other items to achieve the perfection in metal works that you deserve.<br><br>We also fix metal items made by others due to poor construction and craftsmanship.<br><br>We have had clients from Southern Pines, Fort Bragg, and Fayetteville that have needed items fixed that were made by other companies. So if you care about getting a high quality item, build right from the start, send us an email or give us call.</h3></div>

  <div class="mrTitle"><h2 id="mrTitle">How long does it take to make a custom metal work item?</h2></div>
  <div class="mrBody"><h3>This depends on the scope of the project. Most custom orders can be made and shipped within 1 week of confirming the project details.<br><br>
Shipping is from our shop located at 1964 Ray Road, Spring Lake, NC ( 28390 ) and may effect the item arrival date depending on your location.
For clients ordering from Ft. Bragg, Fayetteville, Hope Mills, and Southern Pines we can ship the items to your door, or you can come by the shop for pick up and see some of the other cool items we have.
</h3></div>

<div class="mrTitle"><h2 id="mrTitle">What does a custom metal work item cost?</h2></div>
<div class="mrBody"><h3>Costs vary depending on the scope of work. The average order is for an individual is between $100 to $300.<br><br>
Our Business signs range from $300 to $1,500 depending on size and accents, such as back lighting.<br><br> We also make bulk items for clients, these can range from Tumbler cups ($20-$40) to memorial and awards items ($75-$200).<br><br>If you want something more unique we are always ready to design and fabricate new items. These items can range from fitness equiptment, to key holders, to steel targets.
</h3></div>

<div class="mrTitle"><h2 id="mrTitle">How do I get a metal work order?</h2></div>
<div class="mrBody"><h3>Its EASY! You can email your detailed description of the item and a .jpeg formatted picture by clicking <a href="mailto:joey@JandPMetalWorks.com?Subject=Custom-Order-from-Website">HERE</a> and we will contact you about the pricing and completion date.<br><br>
If you are in Fayetteville, Hope Mills, Raeford, or Southern Pines, feel free to come by the shop!<br><br> We love working with everyone in the Ft Bragg, Fayetteville, Hope Mills, Southern Pines, Raeford, and Spring Lake areas and do our best to make the process easy for you.<br><br>
You can also come visit our shop at 1964 Ray Road, Spring Lake, NC ( 28390 ) and speak with Joey directly. We love new projects and challenges and look forward to yours!<br><br>If you would like to speak to us you can call us at <a href="tel:1-910-497-0104">910-497-0104</a>.
</h3></div>

<div class="mrTitle"><h2 id="mrTitle">Why are our products better than the competition?</h2></div>
<div class="mrBody"><h3>This is simple, our attention to detail, superior craftsmanship, and highest quality materials, make us the best company to hire for your projects.<br><br>Additionally, when you purchase one of our products, you can rest assured that it will last for ages and become an heirloom. We have had to fix many other companies items that were made at a lower quality and started to fall apart.<br><br>Our methods ensure that the items made do not warp over time or loose color and chip. While no product is indestructible, we go the extra mile to make sure your product exceeds the standards of construction that would be seen elsewhere.
</h3></div>

<div class="mrTitle"><h2 id="mrTitle">Need a gift idea?</h2></div>
<div class="mrBody"><h3>Custom metal art is the perfect way to go above and beyond the status quo. Be it an anniversary gift, birthday present, retirement gift, or “just because”, metal art is sure to be the best gift you can give or receive!<br><br>Take your time and browse through some of our work. We have many unique items and many of our clients personalize their metal work by adding their names or family crests.<br><br>Our Tumbler selection is always a best seller. Yeti, Ozark, and RTIC cups are commonly used and easy to mistake for someone elses. Avoid these issues by having us design and powder coat your cup to make it unique, just like you. Cups can be made within a few hours and are perfect for when you are in a rush but need something of quality.
</h3></div>

